score.explanation: Your Wi-Fi network is moderately healthy, but there is room for improvement to reduce dropouts.
score.trend_summary: Since last scan: download improved, upload improved, ping improved, networks increased.

latest_report.diagnosis: The presence of many competing networks likely contributes to your random dropouts. Optimal channel usage and adjustments to your router's settings should improve stability.

performance.interpretation: Your download speed is close to the maximum of your ISP plan, while the upload speed is somewhat lower, but overall latency is acceptable.

problems: High congestion on 2.4GHz band due to multiple networks.
Dropouts may be linked to the location of the router near a bedroom window.
Inadequate upload speed affecting video calls or online gaming.
fixes: Change the 2.4GHz channel to 1 for less interference.
Change the 5GHz channel to 149 to improve stability and reduce congestion.
Consider relocating the router to a more central location in your home to improve coverage.
Enable Quality of Service (QoS) features on your router to prioritize gaming traffic.
Evaluate and minimize device usage on the 2.4GHz band by connecting more devices to the 5GHz band.
